  "description": "Walmart Inc. is a retailer built around a large U.S. grocery and general\u2011merchandise business, with Walmart U.S., Sam\u2019s Club, and Walmart International (including Flipkart in India). It combines supercenters and clubs with e\u2011commerce (Marketplace and Walmart Fulfillment Services), Walmart+ membership, and a growing advertising platform (Walmart Connect). Customers include households nationwide and small businesses via Sam\u2019s Club; competitors include Amazon (e\u2011commerce/ads), Target (mass retail), Costco and BJ\u2019s (clubs), Kroger and Aldi (grocery), Dollar General and Dollar Tree (value), and Temu/Shein in cross\u2011border e\u2011commerce. Key suppliers include major CPG vendors\u2014Procter & Gamble, Unilever, PepsiCo, Coca\u2011Cola, Nestl\u00e9, Kimberly\u2011Clark, and Johnson & Johnson\u2014alongside a large private\u2011label manufacturing base.",
